rComments: Danielle does not provide material or lectures that make the class seem difficult, but her midterm and final exam are insanely hard. The final exam contained extremely specific questions that had nothing to do with actually understanding broader concepts. Studied for days and still knew almost nothing on the final

Dr. Fortin is a really good professor. The tests aren't really difficult if you learn the reactions and can do basic unit transformations. The online assignments are worth 20% of the final grade and they're super easy, you just have to search in the power points and you'll get 100% on all of them. I would recommend this class.
Powerpoints could be more helpful, and lectures are hard to keep up with. Not very generous with marks, and not good at giving feedback or answering questions.

She complained often about having to get around campus and class being so early. She also screwed up her quiz questions and expected us all to notice the announcement she made about it instead of sending us an e-mail so a lot of people unfairly lost points. Her exams are so heavy on chemistry and math that they do not reflect all of the material.

Dr Fortin supervised my undergraduate thesis. If you put the work into it, it isn't difficult to do extremely well with her. She is very helpful, resourceful and she will guide you in the right direction. Loved doing my project under her supervision. I would suggest this Professor to anyone, especially those who are interested in geochemistry.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Dr. Fortin only teaches the first half of the class, but it was my favourite part of the semester. She is very smart and funny. Study hard and memorize which types of reactions are what and you'll do great! Midterms were easy. Just remember to finish the online assignments on time!!! They add up in the long run.

1. Assignments are very poorly done. It is all online and such a hassle to save or come back to assignment later. 2. Her slides are missing 70% of the stuff that matters.  Very bad professor and very boring lectures
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Participation matters']

rComments: The professor is very helpful.I scored really low on the final and went to check my exam to find that she doesn't give part marks for her conversion questions .So guys make sure to know your conversions. They are super useful.I got 0 out of 20 on a question just because i made one wrong conversion. She only looks at final answers.

Dr. Fortin is a great lecturer and conveys concepts in a super easy to understand manner. She is always so smiley and happy, which made the 8:30 am class worth it. Do the online assignments, know how to convert between ppb and g/L, COME TO CLASS and you should do fine.

Prof is passionate and clear and get's you interested in material. HOWEVER, on her exams she only marks for final answers and I got 0 on a five part question because I got the first part wrong on a midterm. Even though lectures cover a lot of material, MT only test the chemistry and the math which she vaguely touches upon.
clear explanation, go to class and you will know what to get
Amazing prof. Very passionate about science which made her lessons a pleasure to listen to.
She covers the first part of the1 course. The material is not difficult and a portion of the grade is easy to get (online assessments straight of the slides). Recommended

Overall good class. The math and chemical equation stuff is rather basic and she tells you everything you need to know to understand it. GO TO CLASS. Only gripe with this class were the online quizzes which you had 48 hours to do(friday + saturday). Not so practical for people that work and party....

I loved the first part of the course taught by this prof.  Well organized, and if you go to class, you will know EXACTLY what to expect on her midterm and her part of the final.  Take a lot of notes, her slides are merely a skeleton of what will be evaluated...  A VERY bare skeleton.  Difficult class to have early in the morning though...

Very nice prof! Yes, she does focus a lot on chemical equations, and math stuff, but this is because she teaches the physical-chemical aspects of the environment. Other prof teaches the biological aspects for the 2nd half of the term. Midterms are not bad at all. Don' waste money on the book though, she only tests you what is covered in the lecture

What a haphazardly organized class...I am a well-organized studious student, but this course...I couldn't get a grasp on it. The lectures teach you one thing,the book teaches you another,and then the exams show you something else.Fortin's ENTIRE emphasis is on chem formulas + anything math-related,barely any Env Sci;what a disappointment of a class
Prof. Fortin is well-organized, gives clear notes, and midterms are fair with no trick questions - she simply tests your knowledge of material presented in a straightforward manner.
